{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4590c303-c087-4041-b24e-d72af239f296","content":"To register your MCP server in the **official MCP Registry** (hosted at [github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers)):\n\n1. **Fork** the `modelcontextprotocol/servers` repo on GitHub.\n2. **Add your server's metadata** as a new entry (typically a JSON/YAML file or a section in the registry's index) following the repo's contribution guidelines.\n3. **Open a Pull Request** against the main branch with your addition.\n4. The maintainers will review and merge it.\n\n**Before submitting**, check the repo's `CONTRIBUTING.md` or `README.md` for the exact format and requirements — they may ask for fields like name, description, NuGet package URL, transport type, etc.\n\nYou can quickly check the current guidelines:\n```\nhttps://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers\n```\n\nWould you like me to fetch the latest contribution instructions from that repo for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ad2ef29c-5c2c-43c5-9bf4-ee98ef80b3df","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to register their C# MCP server in the official MCP Registry. This is a general knowledge question about the MCP (Model Context Protocol) ecosystem. Let me provide what I know and also check for any relevant information online.","outputTokens":302,"requestId":"B01A:2BCA1C:1459133:16C15CC:6A027E47"},"id":"34e26166-c8e4-4ec7-ae0a-ac0ad27f64e9","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:11:43.532Z","parentId":"67b670ea-3130-4e1f-9b5d-f54013b4a11b"}
